Having said that, adultery does give men some additional leverage when it comes to divorce and it can be used to bar the wife's right to the family home among many other legal benefits. Any fees racked up by the husband whilst in adulterous relationships should not be used to offset his obligation to provide the family with maintenance and child support.

International adoption of small children by couples (husband and wife).

Parents getting divorced or separated in Argentina must undergo a process by the Family Court to determine how child support and child custody will be allocated between them. It is vital that the co-parents are capable of raising healthy, well-adjusted kids and both the judge and social worker have the final say over who will be granted primary custody of the small children.

International adoption of small children is also a very common legal process in Argentina with adoptions outside of the country blocked via Federal Law 23737. A variety of adoption groups are also available in Argentina and they can be searched for via a Google search.

Primary custody of small children, which cannot be shared with ex-partners, mothers are usually granted custody (in spite of the common cultural belief). A legal tutor is appointed by the court to safeguard the best interests of the children and they will be the court's one and only representation.
